Class ArrayBiterator

java.lang.Object
com.shouldis.bitset.parallel.Biterator
com.shouldis.bitset.parallel.SizedBiterator
com.shouldis.bitset.parallel.ArrayBiterator
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.Spliterator<java.lang.Integer>, java.util.Spliterator.OfInt, java.util.Spliterator.OfPrimitive<java.lang.Integer,​java.util.function.IntConsumer,​java.util.Spliterator.OfInt>
public final class ArrayBiterator
extends SizedBiterator
Implementation of SizedBiterator used to stream all values within a specified integer array representing indices in an order appropriate to manipulate a BitSet in parallel. The contents of the supplied arrays must be distinct, and sorted in ascending order; behavior is undefined otherwise.
Author:
Aaron Shouldis

  • Constructor Details

    • ArrayBiterator

      public ArrayBiterator​(int[] items, int position, int end)
      Creates a ArrayBiterator with the specified starting and ending indices position and end. The values within the specified range of indices within the array items will be processed.
      Parameters:
      items - the array of indices to be processed.
      position - (inclusive) the first index to include.
      end - (exclusive) the index after the last index to include.
      Throws:
      java.lang.NullPointerException - if items is null.
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if position is greater than or equal to end.

    • ArrayBiterator

      public ArrayBiterator​(int[] items)
      Creates a ArrayBiterator covering the entirety of the specified array. The values within the specified array items will be processed.
      Parameters:
      items - the array of indices to be processed.
      Throws:
      java.lang.NullPointerException - if items is null.
